WASHINGTON Lt.Gen. Lewis
B. Hershey, Director of Selective
Service, has announced the recent
appointment of Col. Campbell c.
Johns on to be Assistant Director
of the Selective Service System.
Colonel Johnson served as Ex-
ecutive Assistant to the Director,
lo4O-l948, and as Assistant to the
Director, I948-1o64.


A native of the District Of
Columbia, Colonel johnson has
been a leader in civic and social
welfare activities in the National
Capital throughout his career.
Among his other activities. he
formerly served as Chairman of
the District of Columbia Par ole
Board; holds office in the YMCA,
is Vice Chairman of the National
Capital Housing Authority; and
taught at Howard University. He
is a member of the Bar of the
District of Columbia and North
Carolina. He holds the Army
Distinguished Service Medal for
his work with the Selective Ser
vice System.
